==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''encyclopaedia'' from Greek ''en'' + ''kyklo(s)'' circle + ''paideia'' children

<!--Hm, this definition looks as though it has been lifted from somewhere.  Do we have permission?-->
# A reference work (often in several volumes) containing in-depth articles on various topics (often arranged in alphabetical order) dealing with a wide range of subjects or with some particular specialty

====Alternative spellings====
*[[encyclopædia]]
*(''chiefly British''): '''encyclopaedia'''.  The spelling '''encyclopedia''' is standard in American, Canadian, Australian and International English and is also common in British English.

